{# ── IN BRIEF — the dataset, one paragraph + firm-level source. Distinct from the §summary tldr above (relocated from frontmatter inBrief, verbatim). prose (sand, read). ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="research-in-brief" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">In brief</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <div class="prose">
      <p><strong>The US QuickBooks Cleanup Benchmarks</strong> is TechBrot&rsquo;s original dataset on the cost, effort, and error profile of QuickBooks file cleanups &mdash; one anonymized row logged at the close of every completed Certified ProAdvisor engagement. Methodology and schema are public now; each benchmark is released only once it reaches a defensible sample. No estimated or fabricated numbers, ever.</p>
      <p class="in-brief__source">Built and maintained by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at TechBrot Inc., an independent firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── DEFINITION — what it is, prose (white, read). (H2: An owned dataset, not a borrowed statistic.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="research-definition">
  <div class="ct read">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">What it is</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">An owned dataset, not a borrowed statistic.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>The <strong>US QuickBooks Cleanup Benchmarks</strong> is a structured record of what TechBrot actually sees when neglected QuickBooks files arrive for cleanup. Most &ldquo;benchmarks&rdquo; in this space are repackaged vendor marketing or a survey of opinions. This one is built the only way a benchmark earns trust: from real, completed, paid engagements &mdash; the files, the hours, and the fees as they genuinely landed.</p>
      <p>It exists because the question owners ask most often &mdash; <em>&ldquo;my books are months behind; what is this going to cost to fix?&rdquo;</em> &mdash; has no honest published answer. A dataset built from real cleanups, transparent about its own sample size, is the only way to answer it without guessing. The dataset is the visible artifact; the discipline behind it &mdash; logging one row at every close &mdash; is the real work, and it cannot be backfilled, which is why it starts now.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── SCHEMA — the 8 logged fields, dc-card r-2 (sand). (H2: Eight fields, logged at every engagement close.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="research-fields" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The schema</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:30ch;margin-bottom:10px;">Eight fields, logged at every engagement close.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 30px;max-width:66ch;">The schema is fixed now &mdash; so the very first row and the thousandth row measure the same things, the same way.</p>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for f in fields %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{{ f.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:15px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ f.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── METHODOLOGY — four rules, process-grid (white). (H2: How each row gets into the dataset.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="research-methodology">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The methodology</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">How each row gets into the dataset.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 30px;max-width:66ch;">Four rules, fixed before the first row &mdash; the difference between a benchmark and a marketing number.</p>
    <div class="process-grid">
      {%- for m in methodology %}
      <div class="process-step">
        <span class="process-step__n">0{{ loop.index }}</span>
        <h3>{{ m.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p>{{ m.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── STATUS — the honest live count (N may be 0). Real config/honesty figures only — NO fabrication. stat band r-4 mono + prose (sand, read). (H2: Honest by design: the live count.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="research-status" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Where the dataset stands today</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:28px;">Honest by design: the live count.</h2>
    <div class="r-4">
      <div><div class="mono" style="font-size:30px;font-weight:500;color:var(--color-accent);">{{ datasetN }}</div><div style="font-size:13px;line-height:1.5;color:var(--color-ink-mute);margin-top:8px;">completed engagements logged</div></div>
      <div><div class="mono" style="font-size:30px;font-weight:500;color:var(--color-accent);">8</div><div style="font-size:13px;line-height:1.5;color:var(--color-ink-mute);margin-top:8px;">fields per record</div></div>
      <div><div class="mono" style="font-size:30px;font-weight:500;color:var(--color-accent);">20</div><div style="font-size:13px;line-height:1.5;color:var(--color-ink-mute);margin-top:8px;">minimum N before any breakdown is reported (50+ preferred)</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="prose" style="margin-top:26px;">
      <p>{% if datasetN == 0 %}The dataset is <strong>live and collecting (N=0).</strong> No statistics are published yet &mdash; and we will not publish one until a breakdown reaches at least 20 real records (we prefer 50 or more), always with the sample size shown. We&rsquo;d rather show a count of zero honestly than a number we can&rsquo;t stand behind.{% else %}The dataset currently holds <strong>{{ datasetN }} completed engagements.</strong> Statistics are published per breakdown only once it reaches at least 20 real records (50+ preferred), always with the sample size disclosed; everything below that threshold stays unreported.{% endif %} The methodology above is locked, so the data is comparable from the first row forward. This page updates as the count grows.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── PROGRAM — six datasets, each with live N (honest, never fabricated). dc-card r-3 (white). (H2: Six original datasets, each built the same honest way.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="research-program">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The research program</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:30ch;margin-bottom:10px;">Six original datasets, each built the same honest way.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 30px;max-width:66ch;">The Cleanup Benchmarks is the flagship; five more datasets log alongside it &mdash; same rules: observed on real engagements, anonymized at source, and never reported on a breakdown below a defensible sample. Each shows its live record count.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for d in datasets %}
      <article class="dc-card"><span class="eyebrow">{% if d.flagship %}Flagship &middot; {% endif %}Collecting &middot; N={{ d.n }}</span><h3>{{ d.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:15px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ d.captures | safe }}</p></article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="prose" style="margin-top:24px;font-size:14px;color:var(--color-ink-mute);"><small>Every dataset is &ldquo;collecting&rdquo; until it reaches a defensible sample. We publish a figure on a breakdown only at a minimum N&ge;20 (50+ preferred), always with the sample size shown &mdash; never a fabricated, estimated, or borrowed number.</small></p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── PLANNED — five reports on the roadmap, dc-card r-3 (sand). (H2: The reports we&rsquo;re building toward.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="research-planned" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">On the roadmap</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:30ch;margin-bottom:10px;">The reports we&rsquo;re building toward.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 30px;max-width:66ch;">Five flagship reports, each drawn from the datasets above. Each releases independently the moment its sample is defensible (minimum N&ge;20, 50+ preferred, sample size disclosed) &mdash; not before.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for p in planned %}
      <article class="dc-card"><span class="eyebrow">{{ p.tag }} &middot; {{ p.status }}</span><h3>{{ p.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:15px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ p.body | safe }}</p></article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── HONESTY — the no-fabrication standard, disclosure banner (white, read). (H2: What you will never find here.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="research-honesty">
  <div class="ct read">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Our standard</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">What you will never find here.</h2>
    <div class="disclosure">
      <div class="disclosure__body"><strong>No fabricated, estimated, or borrowed numbers.</strong> TechBrot publishes no statistic it has not observed on real, completed engagements at a defensible sample size. Until a benchmark is released, there is no number to cite &mdash; and we say so plainly rather than fill the gap with a guess. The dataset is built by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at TechBrot Inc., an independent firm; it carries no client-identifying data and implies no affiliation with Intuit Inc.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── RELATED — cross-links, dc-card hub-card r-3 (sand). (H2: Related work.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="research-related" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Where else to go</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:28px;">Related work.</h2>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for n in related %}
      <a class="dc-card hub-card" href="{{ n.href }}"><h3>{{ n.title | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:15px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ n.body | safe }}</p></a>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
